        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 2:04PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 204 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Berthoud, or 20 miles south of Fort Collins, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Longmont, Firestone, Frederick, Milliken, Dacono, Mead,
Platteville and Fort St Vrain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
